result.execSummary:
The defendant Ulises Velasco Vasquez was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Expose Child to Harmful Material, a class I felony, Wisconsin Statutes 948.11(2)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Defendant was specifically found to not be eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program or the Substance abuse Program. Defendant to receive credit for 230 days served.

superMiscConds.notes: Costs and restitution to be paid on a schedule established by the agent.
Defendant is ordered to pay the $250.00 DNA surcharge, provide a DNA sample for testing through the Dept. of Corrections .

Defendant is to complete a Psychological Evaluation and  a Sex Offender Evaluation, comply with the recommendations and release the findings to the agent.   
Additionally, Defendant shall attend counseling, treatments, programming, evaluations as deemed appropriate by the agent releasing all records to the agent upon request

Defendant is not to have contact with minors under the age of 18 unless authorized by the agent in writing.  
The defendant shall have no contact with  J.S.M.  or her family of any kind, whether direct or indirect, including in person, in writing, by phone, by e-mail or other electronic means, through a third party or in any other way.

supervisions.notes: The defendant shall pay Department of Correction fees as directed by the agent.
